In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1}(peeled and diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}(cored and diced into 1/2-inch pieces). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

Heat a large dry #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%oz}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Transfer bacon to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a medium #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1}, @Mexican spice blend{2%tablespoon}, and @salt{1%tsp}. Season generously with @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir @crushed tomatoes{1}, @mushroom stock concentrate{2}, @kidney beans{1}(with liquid), and @water{1/2%cup} into pot. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium. Simmer until thickened, ~{15-18%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Serve rice, chili, @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz} , @cheddar cheese{1%cup}, @sour cream{6%tablespoon}, and scallions family style and let everyone build their own bowl.

> Don't forget to serve with any extra items you may have ordered to build out your meal!

Serve bacon family style alongside chili bar.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.